This paper is primarily focused on the challenges of training deep convolutional networks with low numerical precision, which is a problem that falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper specifically mentions the use of deep convolutional networks, which suggests that computer vision (cs.CV) is another relevant sub-category. The paper also proposes methods to improve training performance, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper involves experiments to verify the proposed methods, which suggests that data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) may also be relevant.
